money validates you in their eyes
when you have money, you see how high the stakes are for people around you
  the rich are constantly stressed out.. 
  the rich are always focused on bigger and bigger deals and new ideas to fulfill
  the poor have little at stake, there's nothing new happening. always complain about the same things
everybody has a price, even you.
  we all have 24 hours in a day, but our time isn't values the same.
some ppl wont close the gap, so u have to leve them behind. 
  You level up while they remain down - same level beginning..
once you have it, money is overrated, but they dont know it
  the law of diminishing returns:
    a bigger penthouse or an even more expensive car wont alter the quality of our life
ppl want the outcome, the secret to your wealth, not the process
urgency trumps depth in the hierarchy of perceived problems
When you disagree with them they will always say money changed you 
    --> growth and evolution dont sit well with those who benefited from you serving them

If you choose the right partner, the money is fine but you’re still grounded
The poor are emotionally attached to money, while the rich see it as a game ...
    you can buy anything you want in life, if your envestment is paying for it.
    if you want to buy a car, buy an apartment instead and use the money you get from renting out the apartment to pay for the luxury car.
    more and more properties and grow your fortune.. monopoly
    
The more money you have, the more you want to be left alone
  money gives u superpower of saying no
  
Everyone will overcharge you for anything
Most people won’t know you’re rich unless you advertise it ...
    true wealth doesnt want the attention
    most ppl cant tell the difference between a $100 and a 15000$ watch
    they might recognize the brands, if they get close enough, but that's not the case too often
    
People are eager to do you favors
    youre no longer transacting in money, instead its in favors, clouts, network
    if i help you with this, you have to come back with smth of at least the same value
    specialized knowledge
    learn to trade favors based on specialized skills

measure your wealth only in unearned income
  as long as you have to work for money, you're not wealthy.
  if you figured out how to make $1, you can figure out how to make $100, $1000, $10000, $100000
  you have to make the money, not earn the money
  
  money has the power to make more of itself... compound interest
  if u can get urself up to $400k in investable cash, 
    there are safe and low-risk instruments out there such as the s&p500 that historically brought in a %10return on a yearly basis.
    some years the economy is booming and youre getting 20-30%, but it averages out at 10%
    $400k + $40k per year --> your money is earning you $40k per year
    average income in the US - $31,100 per year...
    half of the US working population is earning less than $31,100 per year..
    $1m + $100k per year...
    
    
  
